-- Japanese Bought Net 448.1 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2012-08-08T23:53:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-08/japanese-bought-net-448-1-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Aug. 3 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 448.1 billion yen ($5.7 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 46.4 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 32.6 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 434.3 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 735 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 82.5 billion yen in stocks, and sold 322.7 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 329.9
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
